Specific Guidelines

1. State Management

    React Hooks:
        Use React hooks for state management (useState, useEffect, useContext, useReducer).
        Create custom hooks for reusable logic.
    Context API:
        Use React Context for global state when appropriate.
    Props:
        Pass props explicitly for component-specific state.
    WebTorrent State:
        Manage WebTorrent client state in a dedicated context or custom hook.

2. Performance Optimization

    Lazy Loading:
        Use Next.js dynamic imports for code splitting.
        Implement lazy loading for large components.
    Memoization:
        Use React.memo, useMemo, and useCallback to prevent unnecessary re-renders.
    WebTorrent Optimization:
        Initialize WebTorrent client only when needed.
        Clean up WebTorrent resources when components unmount.

3. WebTorrent Implementation

    Client Initialization:
        Initialize WebTorrent client in a custom hook or context provider.
    Torrent Creation:
        Implement functions to create torrents from files.
    Seeding:
        Manage seeding state and provide UI feedback.
    Downloading:
        Handle torrent downloads with progress tracking.
    WebRTC:
        Configure WebRTC for browser-to-browser communication.
    Tracker Configuration:
        Set up and manage WebTorrent trackers.

4. File Handling

    File Selection:
        Implement drag-and-drop and file picker interfaces.
    File Processing:
        Handle file chunking and processing efficiently.
    File Storage:
        Use appropriate storage methods (IndexedDB, localStorage, etc.).
    File Streaming:
        Implement streaming for media files when possible.

5. UI/UX Guidelines

    Responsive Design:
        Ensure the application works well on all device sizes.
    Loading States:
        Provide clear loading indicators for torrent operations.
    Error Handling:
        Display user-friendly error messages.
    Progress Tracking:
        Show download/upload progress with visual indicators.
    Accessibility:
        Ensure the application is accessible to all users.

6. Next.js Best Practices

    App Router:
        Use the Next.js App Router for routing.
    Server Components:
        Use Server Components where appropriate.
    Client Components:
        Mark components that need client-side interactivity with "use client".
    API Routes:
        Implement API routes for server-side operations.
    Metadata:
        Configure proper metadata for SEO.

7. WebTorrent-Specific Considerations

    Browser Compatibility:
        Handle WebRTC and WebTorrent browser compatibility issues.
    Network Configuration:
        Provide fallbacks for restrictive network environments.
    Peer Discovery:
